snippet.textDisplay:
Machamp can maximize his chances by having perfect IV's (at least in HP, Attack, Defense, Speed, & SpDef in case Goro has some Special Attacks), a Nature that boosts either Attack or Speed at the cost of Special Attack, and EV's to either make him a better tank or sweeper (probably sweeper, with the extra 4 EV's going into HP or Defense), powerful TM's, and: if the battle's gonna go on for a few rounds: Leftovers could make himself heal a bit each turn, or the Shell Bell to give himself Lifesteal; else: a Choice Band to give him a single, spammy attack with more power, a Choice Scarf to make himself spam a single attack more quickly, or Life Orb to try to kill Goro before a combination of Goro's attacks and Life Orb's life-draining drawback kills him. In that last item, he'll finish that fight even if it kills him.




I'm not much of a competitive battler, but if you get a perfect Machop (perfect IV's in at least those stats), one of those 2 Natures, etc, you'd be good to go.




As for Guillotine: this isn't gen 1, and even if he had that move, would you spam it, hoping to kill your opponent in a single hit, or would you rather just kill them the old-fashioned way (No-Holds-Barred Beatdown) that might take fewer turns & be usable for longer?
